From 1634be30836969f1c611e1779952c11548d6d50d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mykola Lysenko <mykolal@meta.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 11:07:56 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] bpf: add UML verification stubs for kernels without perf
 events

UML cannot enable PERF_EVENTS, KPROBE_EVENTS, UPROBE_EVENTS, or the
normal BPF_LSM stack. That leaves tracing, stack trace maps, LSM, and
selected kfunc-backed selftest objects unregistered, so BPF_PROG_LOAD
fails before the verifier can analyze those programs.

Add hidden UML-only verification stubs for kernels without perf events.
The primary BPF_VERIFICATION_STUBS option registers minimal
verifier_ops/prog_ops for tracing program types and provides callchain
stubs so BPF_MAP_TYPE_STACK_TRACE can be created for load-time analysis.
It also provides verification-only bpf_trace_printk and bpf_trace_vprintk
helper prototypes so programs using bpf_printk() can still be verified when
CONFIG_BPF_EVENTS is absent. The helper stubs return -EOPNOTSUPP if ever
executed.

Keep the LSM-facing surface behind a separate hidden
BPF_LSM_VERIFICATION_STUBS option that also requires CONFIG_SECURITY.
That way BPF_PROG_TYPE_LSM and BPF_MAP_TYPE_INODE_STORAGE are only
advertised when the matching stub symbols are compiled.

The stubs are for static analysis only: programs are accepted far enough
for BPF_PROG_LOAD verification, but are never attached or executed.

Signed-off-by: Mykola Lysenko <mykolal@meta.com>
---
 include/linux/bpf_lsm.h             |   6 +-
 include/linux/bpf_types.h           |  10 +-
 include/linux/perf_event.h          |  17 +-
